-- Brazil's economic activity rises 0.4 pct in Sept - central bank
-- 
-- Mon Nov 17, 2014 05:48AM EST
-- None



BRASILIA, Nov 17 (Reuters) - The Brazilian central bank's IBC-Br economic activity index <BRIBC=ECI> rose 0.40 percent in September from August in seasonally adjusted terms, the bank said on Monday.

The median estimate in a Reuters survey of 18 analysts was for a 0.14 percent increase. Economic activity in the third quarter rose a seasonally-adjusted 0.6 percent from the second quarter.